name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: fs.s3a.multipart.purge.age
description:
Minimum age in seconds of multipart uploads to purge
    on startup if "fs.s3a.multipart.purge" is true

name: dfs.ha.tail-edits.rolledits.timeout
description: The timeout in seconds of calling rollEdits RPC on Active NN.

name: hadoop.security.dns.log-slow-lookups.threshold.ms
description:
If slow lookup logging is enabled, this threshold is used to decide if a
    lookup is considered slow enough to be logged.

name: dfs.namenode.missing.checkpoint.periods.before.shutdown
description:
The number of checkpoint period windows (as defined by the property
    dfs.namenode.checkpoint.period) allowed by the Namenode to perform
    saving the namespace before shutdown.

name: dfs.datanode.socket.write.timeout
description: Timeout in ms for clients socket writes to DataNodes.

name: dfs.namenode.reconstruction.pending.timeout-sec
description:
Timeout in seconds for block reconstruction.  If this value is 0 or less,
    then it will default to 5 minutes.

name: dfs.ha.log-roll.period
description:
How often, in seconds, the StandbyNode should ask the active to
    roll edit logs. Since the StandbyNode only reads from finalized
    log segments, the StandbyNode will only be as up-to-date as how
    often the logs are rolled. Note that failover triggers a log roll
    so the StandbyNode will be up to date before it becomes active.
    Support multiple time unit suffix(case insensitive), as described
    in dfs.heartbeat.interval.If no time unit is specified then seconds
    is assumed.
